In [8]:
df['MarkDownSUM'] = df['MarkDown1'] + df['MarkDown2'] + df['MarkDown3'] + df['MarkDown4'] + df['MarkDown5']
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])
df['Week'] = df['Date'].dt.week
df['Month'] = df['Date'].dt.month
df['Quarter'] = df['Date'].dt.quarter
df['Half'] = df['Month'].apply(lambda x: 'H1' if x <= 6 else 'H2')
df['Year'] = df['Date'].dt.year

df['Dept'] = df['Dept'].astype(int)

ASSUMPTION #1¶

  • The higher the markdown value, the higher the weekly sales
In [18]:
sns.set(style="white")

corr = df[["Weekly_Sales","MarkDown1","MarkDown2","MarkDown3","MarkDown4","MarkDown5","MarkDownSUM"]].corr()
mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr, dtype=np.bool))

fig, axes = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6), dpi=150, facecolor=background_color)
cmap = sns.diverging_palette(220, 10, as_cmap=True)
sns.heatmap(corr, mask=mask, cmap=cmap, vmax=1, vmin=-1, center=0,

  • Markdown1-5 and markdown sum have a very weak correlation with the weekly sales so that we will leave these columns out
  • Temperature. Fuel price, CPI, and Unemployment are very weakly correlated with the weekly sales, so these columns will also be dropped out
  • IsHoliday and week will be considered for further analysis as the sales in the holiday weeks are higher than in the non-holiday weeks
  • Department and Store size has a moderate correlation with the weekly sales

the evaluation is based on Weighted Mean Absolute Error (WMAE), with a weight of 5 for Holiday Weeks and 1 otherwise.

In [31]:
def WMAE(df, targets, predictions):
    weights = df.IsHoliday.apply(lambda x: 5 if x else 1)
    return np.round(np.sum(weights*abs(targets-predictions))/(np.sum(weights)), 2)

Random Forest Parameter Tuning¶

In [35]:
def RF_I(n_estimators, max_depth):
    result = []
    for estimator in n_estimators:
        for depth in max_depth:
            print('START:', ', n_estimators:', estimator, ', max_depth:', depth)
            model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=estimator, max_depth=depth, random_state=12).fit(train_inputs, train_targets)
            train_wmae = WMAE(train_inputs, train_targets, model.predict(train_inputs))
            val_wmae = WMAE(val_inputs, val_targets, model.predict(val_inputs))
            result.append({'Max_Depth': depth, 'Estimators': estimator,
                           'WMAE (training)': train_wmae, 'WMAE (validation)': val_wmae})
            print('FINISH')
    return pd.DataFrame(result)

def RF_II(n_estimators, max_depth, max_features):
    result = []
    for feature in max_features:
        print('START:' ', max_features:', feature)
        model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=n_estimators, max_depth=max_depth,
                                      max_features=feature, random_state=12).fit(train_inputs, train_targets)
        train_wmae = WMAE(train_inputs, train_targets, model.predict(train_inputs))
        val_wmae = WMAE(val_inputs, val_targets, model.predict(val_inputs))
        result.append({'Max_Feature': feature, 'WMAE (training)': train_wmae, 'WMAE (validation)': val_wmae})
        print('FINISH')
    return pd.DataFrame(result)

def RF_III(n_estimators, max_depth, max_features, min_samples_split, min_samples_leaf):
    result = []
    for split in min_samples_split:
        for leaf in min_samples_leaf:
            print('START:' ', min_samples_split:', split, ', min_samples_leaf:', leaf)
            model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=n_estimators, max_depth=max_depth,
                                          max_features=max_features, min_samples_leaf=leaf,
                                          min_samples_split=split, random_state=12).fit(train_inputs, train_targets)
            train_wmae = WMAE(train_inputs, train_targets, model.predict(train_inputs))
            val_wmae = WMAE(val_inputs, val_targets, model.predict(val_inputs))
            result.append({'Min_Samples_Leaf': leaf, 'Min_Samples_Split': split,
                           'WMAE (training)': train_wmae, 'WMAE (validation)': val_wmae})
            print('FINISH')
    return pd.DataFrame(result)

Gradient Boosting Machine Parameter Tuning¶

In [45]:
def GBM_I(n_estimators, max_depth):
    result = []
    for estimator in n_estimators:
        for depth in max_depth:
            print('START:', ', n_estimators:', estimator, ', max_depth:', depth)
            model = XGBRegressor(n_estimators=estimator, max_depth=depth, random_state=12).fit(train_inputs, train_targets)
            train_wmae = WMAE(train_inputs, train_targets, model.predict(train_inputs))
            val_wmae = WMAE(val_inputs, val_targets, model.predict(val_inputs))
            result.append({'Max_Depth': depth, 'Estimators': estimator,
                           'WMAE (training)': train_wmae, 'WMAE (validation)': val_wmae})
            print('FINISH')
    return pd.DataFrame(result)

def GBM_II(n_estimators, max_depth, learning_rate):
    result = []
    for lr in learning_rate:
        print('START:' ', learning_rate:', lr)
        model = XGBRegressor(n_estimators=n_estimators, max_depth=max_depth,
                                      learning_rate=lr, random_state=12).fit(train_inputs, train_targets)
        train_wmae = WMAE(train_inputs, train_targets, model.predict(train_inputs))
        val_wmae = WMAE(val_inputs, val_targets, model.predict(val_inputs))
        result.append({'learning_rate': lr, 'WMAE (training)': train_wmae, 'WMAE (validation)': val_wmae})
        print('FINISH')
    return pd.DataFrame(result)
